(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.606, compare 3rd-4th c.AD: Tryphiodorus Epicus 230 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μαινόμενος οἶνος a <b>hot, strong</b> wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 773d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of feelings, ἐλπὶς μαινομένη Oracle texts cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.77; ἔρις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 935 (Lyric poetry); ἄχεα 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 957 (Lyric poetry); μαινομένᾳ ξὺν ὁρμᾷ [prev. author] “Ant.” 135 (Lyric poetry); σὺν μ. δόξᾳ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 887 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> ἄμπελος μαινομένη, of a vine that is never done bearing fruit, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Mirabilia” 846a38, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 1.18.4. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> μαινόμενα ἕλκη <b>malignant</b> ulcers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Asclepiades Epigrammaticus cited in 6th c.AD: Aëtius Medicus 15.14. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>aorist 1</i> <i>active</i> ἔμηνα, in causal sense, <b>madden</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 520 (troch., probably in “IA” 580 (Lyric poetry)), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Thesmophoriazusae” 561 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>enrage</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.4.8: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>present</i> μαίνω first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Hymni” 71.6. (Cf. μέμονα.) \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3105","accentedUnicode":"μαίνομαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0143","matchingForm":"αἰσθάνομαι","stepTransliteration":"aisthanomai","gloss":"to perceive","_zh_t